Patrick Hlomane has been charged in connection with attacks on five women near Rhodes Memorial. CAPE TOWN - The alleged University of Cape Town serial rapist now faces 28 charges which include rape and aggravated assault. Patrick Hlomane's pre-trial hearing in the Western Cape High Court was postponed yesterday because his lawyer was not available. He's been charged in connection with attacks on five women near Rhodes Memorial between November 2015 and January this year. The State has a list of 44 witnesses. The indictment details how Hlomane allegedly accosted the five women at knife point before he would then rape or sexually assault them before taking their valuables. The charges carry a minimum sentence of 20 years for a repeat offender.